  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. The slope is (0 &minus; (&minus;2))/(4 &minus; 0) = &frac12;. The <i>y</i>-intercept is (0, &minus;2), so <i>b</i> = &minus;2. Thus <i>y</i> = &frac12;<i>x</i> &minus; 2.</p><p>Choice B uses the wrong slope. Choices C and D use incorrect signs or values for both slope and intercept.</p>",
